# Presentation Components

## Failure display
Listen to `state.failure` in `BlocListener`. Use `failure.message ?? failure.defaultMessage(context)` — never a generic fallback key.
`failure.defaultMessage(context)` (`core/error/failure_x.dart`) returns the correct localized message per failure type.

| `FailureType` | Component | Call |
|---------------|-----------|------|
| `snackbar` | `BaseSnackbar` | `.error / .warning / .info / .success(context, message:)` |
| `banner` | `BaseDialog` | `BaseDialog.showBanner(context, message:)` |
| `alert` | `BaseDialog` | `BaseDialog.showBasic(context, ...)` |
| `fullScreenError` | `BaseDialog` | `BaseDialog.showFullscreen(context, ...)` |
| `inlineError` | — | Mapped to `FieldState.error` in BLoC — nothing to do in UI |
| `silent` | — | No UI (cancelled request / analytics only) |

```dart
BlocListener<ThemeBloc, ThemeState>(
  listenWhen: (prev, curr) => curr.failure != null && prev.failure != curr.failure,
  listener: (context, state) {
    final failure = state.failure;
    if (failure == null) return;
    final message = failure.message ?? failure.defaultMessage(context);
    switch (failure.type) {
      case FailureType.snackbar:
        BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: message);
      case FailureType.banner:
        BaseDialog.showBanner(context, message: message);
      case FailureType.alert:
        BaseDialog.showBasic(context,
          title: context.l10n.errorTitle,
          description: message,
          primaryLabel: context.l10n.ok,
          barrierDismissible: false,
        );
      case FailureType.fullScreenError:
        BaseDialog.showFullscreen(context,
          title: context.l10n.errorTitle,
          bodyText: message,
          primaryLabel: context.l10n.retry,
          onPrimary: () => context.read<ThemeBloc>().add(const ThemeStarted()),
          barrierDismissible: false,
        );
      case FailureType.inlineError:
        break;
      case FailureType.silent:
        break;
    }
  },
)
```

## Buttons — always use project components
Never use raw Flutter buttons (`FilledButton`, `ElevatedButton`, `OutlinedButton`, `TextButton`, `IconButton`).

| Component | Factories | Default `expand` |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------|
| `BaseFilledButton` | `.primary()`, `.secondary()` | `true` / `false` |
| `BaseElevatedButton` | `.primary()`, `.secondary()` | `true` / `false` |
| `BaseOutlinedButton` | `.primary()`, `.secondary()` | `true` / `false` |
| `BaseTextButton` | `.primary()`, `.secondary()` | `false` / `false` |
| `BaseIconButton` | `.standard()`, `.primary()`, `.secondary()` | n/a |

All accept `loading: bool` and `disabled: bool`. Pass `null` to `onPressed` to implicitly disable.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
BaseFilledButton.primary(
  onPressed: () => context.read<UserConfigEditBloc>().add(const UserConfigSavePressed()),
  label: context.l10n.save,
  loading: state.status == StateStatus.loading,
)
BaseIconButton.standard(icon: const Icon(Icons.close), onPressed: () => context.router.maybePop())

// ❌ BAD
FilledButton(onPressed: _onSave, child: Text('Save'))
```

## Dialogs and bottom sheets
Never call `showDialog` or `showModalBottomSheet` directly. Use project components from `lib/src/components/dialogs/`.

- **`BaseDialog`** — confirmations, critical errors, blocking choices
- **`BaseBottomSheet`** — selection lists, option menus, non-blocking contextual actions

```dart
// Dialog
BaseDialog.showBasic(context,
  title: context.l10n.confirmTitle,
  description: context.l10n.confirmDescription,
  primaryLabel: context.l10n.confirm,
  onPrimary: _onConfirm,
  secondaryLabel: context.l10n.cancel,
  barrierDismissible: false,
);

// Bottom sheet — selection (returns chosen index)
final index = await BaseBottomSheet.showSelect(context,
  title: context.l10n.selectLanguage,
  options: [context.l10n.english, context.l10n.russian, context.l10n.kazakh],
  selectedIndex: state.selectedLocaleIndex,
);

// Bottom sheet — list of actions
BaseBottomSheet.showList(context,
  title: context.l10n.options,
  items: [
    BaseDialogListItem(label: context.l10n.edit, onTap: _onEdit),
    BaseDialogListItem(label: context.l10n.delete, onTap: _onDelete),
  ],
);
```
